{"text": "of the BdG Hamiltonian in Eq. 74 closes at k = 0. In fact, this closure of the gap can\n\nbe understood in terms of an application of Kitaev\u2019s topological invariant in Eq. 45 to the\n\nspinful superconductor, which is written as\n\nQ = sgn[Pf[\u03c3y\u03c4yHBdG(k = 0)]],\n\n(106)\n\nin particle-hole symmetric systems where \u201cPf\u201d stands for the Pfaffian. One key difference\n\nis that because of the different Nambu basis we use for spinful superconductors, the particle-\n\nhole matrix in the Kitaev Hamiltonian \u03c4x is replaced by \u03c4x \u2192\u03c3y\u03c4y. In addition, for the\n\ncontinuum system used to model systems such as the superconducting nanowire, the k = \u03c0\n\nterm in Eq. 45 is trivial and may be dropped. By computing this Pfaffian for the 4 \u00d7 4\n\nmatrix using the standard definition94 we get\n\nQ = \u03bc2 + \u22062 \u2212V 2\n\nZ,\n\n(107)\n\nwhich is exactly the C0 topological number (see Eq. 94) we obtained from studying vortices\n\nand edges.\n\nD.\n\nDimensional reduction to one dimensional Nanowires\n\nMajorana modes can also be realized in the one dimensional analog of the semiconductor-\n\nsuperconductor structure. This structure is experimentally simpler because one does not\n\nrequire a magnetic insulator to generate the Zeeman field. In the one dimensional case, the\n\nZeeman field can be generated by a magnetic field parallel to the semiconductor supercon-\n\nductor wire. In this case, the Zeeman field cannot generate substantial undesired orbital\n\neffects that would suppress superconductivity, though a finite diameter of the wire can leave\n\nresidual effects95,96.\n\nUnderstanding the one dimensional nanowire does not require any new calculations. The\n\nBdG Hamiltonian Eq. 96 that we used to study the spectrum of domain wall states at ky = 0\n\n42\n\nSuperconductor\n\nnanowire\n\nSTM\n\nE\n\nk\n\n(a)\n\n(b)\n\nMagnetic field\n\nFIG. 4.\n\nThe one dimensional semiconductor superconductor heterostructure allows the appli-\n\ncation of a Zeeman field by a parallel magnetic field.", "embedding": [0.019752482, -0.007480711, -0.005358207, 0.03448836, 0.0012871114, -0.030227836, 0.021892402, -0.025092907, -0.061333213, 0.06742428, 0.027496563, -0.03778431, 0.032647636, -0.042204656, -0.020111436, 0.0301845, -0.016931335, -0.034365878, -0.08450725, 0.012180126, 0.04931264, -0.009999803, -0.04755499, -0.039335288, -0.011490605, 0.058281507, 0.0045284205, 0.03614539, 0.02828614, 0.009447366, 0.04672613, -0.03717095, 0.0034390239, -0.03220762, 0.0047443174, 0.028296463, -0.01973525, -0.05661506, 0.049271785, -0.020733682, 0.07061668, -0.024822848, 0.010338764, -0.011446317, -0.027473092, -0.00069192325, -0.024545884, 0.019118188, -0.010368256, -0.10005695, -0.00081224844, 0.009902728, 0.06685755, -0.003910441, -0.00658114, -0.012952152, 0.0025248863, -0.0024257386, -0.0267134, -0.031163177, 0.006577324, -0.029475437, 0.0069293506, -0.055204842, 0.00888186, 0.03216891, 0.003621884, 0.054710146, -0.0054249438, -0.045303684, -0.0066296775, -0.007420403, -0.004957808, 0.009771144, -0.025919583, 0.03172964, 0.0032545426, -0.0702285, -0.07984447, -0.014240148, -0.027021414, 0.009338217, -0.016248994, 0.0096353395, 0.006407149, -0.031532206, -0.014793978, -0.02386987, -0.013621412, 0.019623613, 0.04576341, 0.044102732, -0.004500861, 0.016612755, 0.034469992, 0.0105614215, 0.008254943, 0.030562488, 0.0278088, 0.011620561, 0.0063983644, 0.06384649, -0.021268344, 0.048412725, -0.03950036, 0.03472238, 0.004207472, 0.0039301016, 0.022649901, -0.043923166, 0.029376872, 0.024746811, 0.013729891, 0.037201665, -0.02313119, 0.017751953, 0.015256989, 0.018653475, -0.040187642, -0.013477732, -0.033472374, -0.024962557, 0.07925128, 0.01918918, -0.031150643, -0.010618113, 0.034557976, 0.018829752, -0.011689067, -0.0036962791, 0.02509512, 0.019139096, -0.01858519, 0.022092598, -0.022187013, 0.022919042, -0.025943594, 0.0025468294, 0.01917766, 0.010270687, 0.03622074, -0.02099312, 0.005772798, 0.